title: Launch Roundup: Falcon Heavy returns with GOES-U, Firefly launches an Alpha
summary: Following a week in which Tropical Storm Alberto brought high seas, wind, and rain-related delays to the launch schedule in Florida, SpaceX hopes to get back on track this week with launches planned for all three of the active Falcon launch pads, including a Falcon Heavy.

title: NASA’s ELaNa 43 Prepares for Firefly Aerospace Launch
summary: NASA is readying for the launch of several small satellites to space, built with the help of students, educators, and researchers from across the country, as part of the agency’s CubeSat Launch Initiative. title: NASA CubeSats Loaded for Launch
summary: Eight CubeSats that are part of NASA’s CubeSat Launch Initiative have been integrated into Firefly Aerospace’s deployment hardware and are ready to be encapsulated into the payload fairing of Firefly’s Alpha rocket.
